    <item>
      <title>Setting up org-mode pdf export in OS X ElCapitan</title>
      <link>http://kirang.in/post/setting-up-org-mode-pdf-export-in-osx-elcapitan/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 30 Nov 2015 00:00:00 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://kirang.in/post/setting-up-org-mode-pdf-export-in-osx-elcapitan/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;basic-tex&#34;&gt;Basic TeX&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Download and install Basic TeX package from &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.tug.org/mactex/morepackages.html&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;set-system-path&#34;&gt;Set System Path&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The package will be installed at &lt;code&gt;/Library/TeX/texbin/&lt;/code&gt;, so it&#xA;must be added to your PATH like so:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;color:#c6d0f5;background-color:#303446;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;table style=&#34;border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#c6d0f5;background-color:#303446;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#838ba7&#34;&gt;1&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#c6d0f5;background-color:#303446;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#99d1db&#34;&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f2d5cf&#34;&gt;PATH&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#99d1db;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f2d5cf&#34;&gt;$PATH&lt;/span&gt;:/Library/TeX/texbin&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Run &lt;code&gt;which latex&lt;/code&gt; to ensure that the path has been set correctly.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;install-dependencies&#34;&gt;Install Dependencies&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You&amp;rsquo;re not ready yet. There are a few more packages that need to be installed&#xA;in order to render the pdf from the tex file. Install them like so:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
